comments: The contact between Osman (CLE), Birch (TOR) and Rubio (CLE) is incidental during the loose ball.
VanVleet (TOR) makes contact to Allen's (CLE) arm that affects his ability to rebound.
Barnes (TOR) makes marginal contact to Mobley's (CLE) body during the drive.
Mobley (CLE) reaches his arm backwards towards Barnes (TOR) but does not affect his ability to defend the play.
Osman (CLE) makes no contact with Anunoby's (TOR) arm during the start of the drive.
Osman (CLE) makes marginal contact to VanVleet's (TOR) arm during the pick that does not affect his SBQR.
Trent Jr. (TOR) makes contact to the ball and no contact to Sexton's (CLE) arm during his drive.
Trent Jr.'s (TOR) hand is out of bounds when he dives and makes contact with the loose ball.
Trent Jr. (TOR) makes contact with the ball as Sexton (CLE) goes up for the shot and dislodges it, causing him to return to the floor with possession of the ball.  A held ball is correctly called.
After Sexton (CLE) taps the jump ball, he and Trent Jr. (TOR) make marginal contact with each other.
Garland (CLE) makes marginal contact with Birch's (TOR) arm with his off-arm during the drive.
Anunoby (TOR) trips Garland (CLE) and the contact affects his driving shot attempt.
